A(\omega)
c/(1-(1-c)e^{-i\omega})
(x_n)_{n\in\mathbb{N}}
f_n
f_0 = 0
f_{n+1} = (1-c)f_n + c\cdot x_{n+1}
f_n = Ae^{i\omega n}
x_n = e^{i\omega n}
f_{n+1} = e^{i\omega (n+1)} = e^{i\omega} e^{i\omega n} = e^{i\omega} f_n
e^{i\omega} A e^{i\omega n} = (1-c)Ae^{i\omega n} + c e^{i\omega} e^{i\omega n}
A(\omega) = \frac{c}{1 - (1-c)e^{-i\omega}}
x_n = \sin(\omega n) = \frac1{2i}(e^{i\omega n}-e^{-i\omega n})
f_n = \frac1{2i}(A(\omega)e^{i\omega n}-\bar A(\omega)e^{-i\omega n}) = |A(\omega)| \sin(\omega n + \phi)
A(\omega) =: |A(\omega)| e^{i\phi}
